@DataProvider & @Factory both are Annotations under TestNg
 
@DataProvider: It is annotation used by TestNG to execute the test method multiple numbers of times
based on the data provided by the DataProvider. Used to supply test data to test methods. This can 
be useful when you need to test a single method with different sets of input dataIt works on 2d 
Array. Only 1 instance(object) of class is required that too gets created implicitly no needs to
created on your own. Can be run directly with @Test Annotation with the dataProvider name provided.

@Factory: It is annotation used by the TestNG to execute the test methods present in the same test class using different instances of the respective class.
It works on 1d Array. Multiple instance(object) of class needs to be created.